Eskom CEO Andre de Ruyter has come under fire for admitting that he introduced some potential contractors to the utility. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Eskom CEO Andre de Ruyter has come under fire for admitting that he introduced some potential contractors to the utility. READ: Eskom to implement Stage 1 load-shedding Eskom spokesperson Sikonathi Mantshantsha has defended the power utility's CEO. De Ruyter has come under fire for introducing some potential contractors to the utility. "On a daily basis the officials including the CEO get approached by people and shown business cards," said Mantshantsha. READ: All Eskom solutions will be resisted: analyst He explained the process is to consider them for the supply chain list. "All the rules are being followed by registering all these suppliers and when there is any business to be done, they go to the pool and the tender gets advertised," Mantshantsha said. He emphasised the Public Finance Management Act is strictly followed in all these cases.